make esp serial connection like sign-in, with esp flash holding difficult-to-fake device identity information along with a private randomly generated password

link esp accounts with scratch accounts using interactive program-based auth: an author can create and share a sketch that contains a keyword (like the MAC address of the esp32), and that should prove that they are the owner of the account, and the website can associate their esp's mac address with it (website has no executive Scratch interaction, but allowing users to claim games in the gallery will be nice among other things)

esp->scratch link is not high-stakes and can be revoked at will

serial connection: signin-like transient site state; game compilation: card view interactive session with gallery navigation


